---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Financial Services Software Delivery" description="Predictable software delivery for financial services companies. KYC/AML, audit trails, and regulatory compliance — delivered on forecast." fullWidth>

  <div class="hero-dark hero-centered">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Finance</span>
      <h1>Software delivery built for<br><em>audit-ready environments</em></h1>
      <p class="hero-subtext">Financial services software ships under regulatory scrutiny. Every feature, every data flow, every deployment needs to withstand examination. Your delivery process should too.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="ind-challenges">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <h2 class="section-heading">The problem with financial software</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Financial services technology has constraints that standard development processes aren't designed to handle.</p>

      <div class="steps-grid">
        <div class="step-cell">
          <h3>KYC/AML Requirements</h3>
          <p>Know Your Customer and Anti-Money Laundering aren't features — they're foundational constraints. Every user flow, every transaction, every data store needs to account for compliance from the architecture level up.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-cell">
          <h3>Audit Trail Visibility</h3>
          <p>Regulators and auditors need to trace every action through the system. That means immutable logging, version-controlled configurations, and documentation that proves what was built, when, and why.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-cell">
          <h3>Data Handling Standards</h3>
          <p>Financial data has strict handling requirements — encryption at rest and in transit, access controls, data residency rules. These aren't optional features to add later. They shape every technical decision.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-cell">
          <h3>Regulatory Compliance</h3>
          <p>SEC, FINRA, state regulators — financial services operates under multiple overlapping regulatory frameworks. Your development process either accounts for all of them or creates risk with every release.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="ind-solution">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Predictive Delivery</span>
      <h2>How we solve it</h2>
      <p>Predictive delivery gives financial services teams a development process that's as disciplined and auditable as the systems they're building.</p>
      <ul class="ind-solution-list">
        <li><strong>Compliance architecture from day one.</strong> KYC/AML requirements, data handling standards, and audit logging are built into the delivery architecture — not bolted on before launch.</li>
        <li><strong>Every delivery is auditable.</strong> Each delivery in NolteOS has a clear scope, acceptance criteria, validation record, and timestamp. Your compliance team gets the documentation trail they need without asking for it.</li>
        <li><strong>Forecasted timelines for regulatory windows.</strong> NolteOS maps your delivery plan against real regulatory deadlines. You'll know whether you're on track for a compliance milestone weeks before it arrives.</li>
        <li><strong>Fixed price, zero ambiguity.</strong> Every delivery has a committed price and definition of done. No surprise costs when regulatory requirements surface mid-build. No invoices for time spent understanding compliance.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="case-studies">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Proven in production</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Real financial services software, delivered predictably.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="case-grid ind-case-single">
      <div class="case-card">
        <div class="case-card-top">
          <span class="case-card-logo-text">Pilou</span>
          <div class="case-card-metrics">
            <span class="case-metric">85 <span class="case-metric-label">deliveries</span></span>
            <span class="case-metric">96% <span class="case-metric-label">accuracy</span></span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="case-card-body">
          <div class="case-card-meta-line">
            <span class="case-pill">Finance</span>
            <span class="case-stage">Series B</span>
          </div>
          <h3>Pilou</h3>
          <p class="case-desc">Financial services platform built under regulatory and compliance requirements. Full audit trail visibility from day one across every delivery.</p>
          <div class="case-meta">
            <div class="case-meta-item"><span class="case-meta-value">2 years</span><span class="case-meta-label">Partnership</span></div>
            <div class="case-meta-item"><span class="case-meta-value">85</span><span class="case-meta-label">Deliveries</span></div>
            <div class="case-meta-item"><span class="case-meta-value">96%</span><span class="case-meta-label">Accuracy</span></div>
            <div class="case-meta-item"><span class="case-meta-value">KYC/AML</span><span class="case-meta-label">Compliance</span></div>
          </div>
          <a class="case-link" href="/work/pilou">Read the full case study &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="predictability-cta">
    <div class="predictability-cta-inner">
      <div class="predictability-cta-content">
        <div class="os-tag">NolteOS <span class="live-dot"></span></div>
        <h2>See what predictable financial services delivery looks like.</h2>
        <p>Describe what you're building. NolteOS forecasts the scope, timeline, and cost — before you commit a single line of code.</p>
        <a class="btn-accent" href="https://os.nolte.io">See Your Forecast</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</Base>

<style>
  .ind-challenges {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--white);
  }
  .ind-solution {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--gray-100);
  }
  .ind-solution h2 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
  }
  .ind-solution p {
    max-width: 640px;
    color: var(--gray-600);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .ind-solution-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 2rem 0 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 640px;
  }
  .ind-solution-list li {
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--gray-600);
  }
  .ind-solution-list strong {
    color: var(--black);
  }
  .ind-case-single {
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .case-studies {
    padding: 5rem 0;
  }
</style>
